<p style="margin: 0px;">Your education and personal development are a high priority when you work for Bank of America. We provide several options for contributing to your own and others' education.</p>
<ul>
	<li><a href="http://www.bankofamerica.com/foundation/index.cfm?template=fd_joemartin" class="body2">Bank of America Joe Martin scholarship program.</a> Offers financial assistance for college or vocational schools to dependent children of associates who have been employed at Bank of America for at least one year</li>
	<li><span class="body2">Tuition reimbursement.</span> Covers education expenses for all associates taking graduate or undergraduate courses at an accredited college or university who meet grade and other eligibility criteria</li>
	<li><span class="body2">Volunteer time for schools.</span> Allows full-time associates to volunteer up to two paid hours per week in public or private schools (pre-school through grade 12)</li>
</ul>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 6px 0px;">
<span class="body2">Tuition Reimbursement</span></p>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 6px 0px;">The tuition reimbursement program helps you pay for college tuition and tuition-related expenses to make it easier to pursue your educational goals.
Features</p>
<ul>
	<li>You may request reimbursement up to the maximum amount allowed each calendar year with no limit on the number of course(s) credit hours taken</li>
	<li>For eligible undergraduate courses, you may be reimbursed up to $2,000 each calendar year. Your reimbursement is considered non-taxable income.</li>
	<li>For eligible graduate courses, you may be reimbursed up to $4,000 each calendar year. Your reimbursement is considered non-taxable income.</li>
</ul>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 6px 0px;"><span class="body2">Eligibility</span></p>
<ul>
	<li>US-based associates who are actively employed at the time the course begins and remain employed at the time of reimbursement</li>
	<li>Courses through an accredited college or university as published by the American Council on Education. The course does not have to be job or business-related and associate does not have to be completing a degree.</li>
</ul>

